The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Bus falls into gorge, 45 killed
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Bus falls into gorge, 45 killed
                            
	Shimla, Nov. 4 (PTI): As many as 45 people died when a private bus fell into a 200metre-deep gorge near Kufri today.        
	The bus, on its way to Shimla from Koti Ghat, rolled into the gorge near Lambi Dhar, about 5km from tourist spot Kufri. The bus was totally smashed after the fall.        
	Forty-four passengers died on the spot and one succumbed to injuries at the Indira Gandhi Medical College in Shimla, SP Rajendra Mohan Sharma said.        
	Five persons were injured in the accident on the Rampur-Shimla road around 11 this morning. There were many women among the dead, police said.        
	The injured have been admitted in the Shimla medical college. The cause of the accident has yet to be known, the police added.        
	A team of Indo-Tibetan Border Police from Shimla rescued eight injured passengers. The team had standard gear like ropes, lightweight stretchers and an ambulance.                                                                                                                                                                          
